{
  "texts": [
    "This will allow the targeting of EUDR and REDD+ mitigation efforts towards specific proximate deforestation drivers in order to achieve more impact.",
    "Another study by 79 used a sample-based citizen science approach for identification of land use following deforestation, while 7,15,27 used a sample-based approach to interpret land use following deforestation visually.",
    "One drawback of these approaches is that they are not wall-to-wall, and they may miss out on many deforestation drivers in unsampled locations, reducing their usefulness for deriving global statistics or getting a general overview 7, 27.",
    "However, these efforts are important for obtaining data useful for developing models used in deriving wall-to-wall maps of land use following deforestation that map every location where deforestation occurred.",
    "Specifically, in combination with deep learning and AL, we show that these data sources have great potential to contribute to obtaining maps for monitoring land use following deforestation."
  ]
}